1.title: Episode #1.1
1.plot: These days we all seem rather nervous about global domination don't we? Well don't fret because our three reluctant hosts have been dragged into the 'minion city' to put a stop to any such stupidity.

2.title: Episode #1.2
2.plot: From the inaugural GR8 Summit to the government building of the Angry Mass, things are about to get surreal as Politics and Religion get FIA'd.

3.title: Episode #1.3
3.plot: From roots, routes, and family trees, leading to an exploration that spans both time and space before arriving 300 miles underground, three idiots are about to make history.

4.title: Episode #1.4
4.plot: Get ready for the most epic adventure yet as the oppressors set an online challenge, leading to some stupid misunderstandings, dividing the team.

5.title: Episode #1.5
5.plot: Our three reluctant hosts find themselves on vacation (whatever that is?), which ultimately leads to adventure and chips.

6.title: Episode #1.6
6.plot: In this extended season finale, the three (anti) heroes go on the hunt for a world famous celebrity.

imdb.plot outline: A once noble scholar had reached his breaking point with earthly matters and so he reached out to the Devil himself and forced a deal; this would become known to many as the tale of 'Faust's infernal acquisition of infinite knowledge'. Of course, this story only works to glorify Faust - the truth is that upon receiving the Infernal Acquisition, the man outsmarted the Devil, enrolled a squad of Hell's most oppressing Imps and began to purge all topics and trends that pestered him, with the intention of erasing such thoughts from humanity itself. Project: Faust's Infernal Acquisition (FIA) shares the events of three unlucky supernatural chaps that got dragged into all this nonsense; #RebelZen, a minor demon rogue from the fourth gate of the forth plateau, near the fourth cave on the shores of the sea of suffering in Hell; #UnicornSlayer, a friendly neighbourhood Barbarian of unknown origin who lives only to slay all Unicorns; and of course, #UrbanOracle, a techno-mage from the near, distant or far future version of some place.
